  <number_of_infrataxa>Genera ca. 27, species ca. 219 (3 genera, 12 species in the flora):</number_of_infrataxa>
  <general_distribution>mostly tropical and subtropical areas of Central America</general_distribution>
  <general_distribution>South America</general_distribution>
  <general_distribution>Africa</general_distribution>
  <general_distribution>Asia</general_distribution>
  <general_distribution>and Australia</general_distribution>
  <general_distribution>some species are widely introduced and established in local floras.</general_distribution>
  <discussion>Plucheeae were segregated from traditionally circumscribed Inuleae by Anderberg in 1989 (see discussion in A. A. Anderberg 1994b).</discussion>
